  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: When user sent > 4 messages with 2 lines of text (8-9 words), the keyboard starts lagging. The performance is so poor that it's almost impossible to efficiently type new messages. When the chat is left and opened again, all works fine until another 4 messages are sent. \r\n\r\nThe issue appears only on Android in all types of chats (1-1, public). I used Samsung Galaxy S8 (native keyboard) to test it. But can be reproduced on another devices as well.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Go to 1-1 chat\r\n- Send 4 messages with 8 words each\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: nightly, 15 June\r\n* Operating System: Android only\r\n* [Slack thread](https://status-im.slack.com/archives/C8KB9DR60/p1529075554000530) about it \r\n* [TF session](https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803622-status/builds/8496015/sessions/4394094867/?accessToken=3FxTuruxjCcADvQNik51WYljyUw) with the issue reproduced on Pixel XL",
